# ORIG TITLE    Bayern Munich on the brink of Champions League final . 
# ORIG CONTENT  German giants Bayern Munich took a huge step towards reaching the final of the Champions League after they outclassed Barcelona 4-0 in the first leg at the Allianz Arena on Tuesday. German international Thomas Mueller opened the scoring in the 25th minute before Mario Gomez doubled the hosts’ advantage from close range just after the restart. Former Chelsea winger Arjen Robben added a third with a superb individual effort on 73 minutes before Mueller made sure of the win by converting David Alaba’s cross eight minutes from the end. The second leg gets underway in Barcelona on May 1. 
